The paper deals with deep learning methods applied to image classification in computational pathology, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The focus is on dealing with label scarcity, which is a common problem in machine learning, and the paper compares unsupervised, semi-supervised, and supervised learning methods. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL), as well as information retrieval (cs.IR) since the paper discusses the use of immunohistochemistry (IHC) stained data to improve classification performance.
